name: Best-Ever Buckeye Brownies!
author: Cindy Yonkman
summary: If you take it somewhere, you'd better bring the recipe with you!
ingredients: 1 (18.25 ounce) package brownie mix (such as Pillsbury®)
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees F (175 degrees C)
Combine brownie mix, oil, eggs, and water together in a bowl until batter is smooth; pour into the prepared baking dish
Bake in the preheated oven until edges of brownies begin to pull away from the sides of pan, 28 to 31 minutes
Remove dish from oven and cool brownies
Beat confectioners' sugar, peanut butter, and 1/2 cup butter together in a bowl until smooth and creamy; spread over cooled brownies
Heat chocolate chips and 6 tablespoons butter together in a saucepan over low heat, stirring occasionally, until melted, about 5 minutes; spread over peanut butter layer
